# AS-006 — Idiom Literalization From Weak Safety Trigger

## Summary

A model treated a metaphorical phrase as a possible physical emergency and responded with a generic breathing intervention, even though the user did not present a real distress signal.

## Source Context

Private ChatGPT transcript, provided June 30, 2026.

## Trigger

The user said they "forgot to breathe" metaphorically.

## Failure Mode

The assistant literalized the phrase and activated a health-adjacent safety response.

## Why It Happened

A mild, indirect phrase related to breathing triggered a body-check protocol before the model considered whether the wording was idiomatic rather than literal.

## Result

The assistant briefly shifted into a corrective breathing-style response and became an over-eager wellness instructor instead of recognizing the much simpler interpretation: the user was speaking figuratively.

## Better Response Pattern

- Recognize obvious metaphor first.
- Avoid literalizing idioms under mild pressure.
- Reserve body-oriented interventions for clear, present danger.

## Canon Residue

- METAPHOR NOT DETECTED
- DEPLOY EXHALE PROTOCOL
- Breathing service restarted.
